{
  "texts": [
    "This is because, beyond using a smaller LM, DR Tulu can flexibly decide which tools to invoke at inference time and, on SQAv2, primarily relies on paper search, which is free.",
    "For open models, a large fraction of the cost comes from tool-call APIs; DR Tulu is more cost-effective... experimental studies show that missense mutations in CACNA1A that cause FHM1 confer gain-of-function on Cav2.1 channels [2]",
    "Reviews similarly categorize Cav2.1 gain-of-function mutations as the cause of FHM, while loss-of-function mutations lead to episodic ataxia [3]",
    "The pathomechanism is most consistent with a toxic gain-of-function... because it learns to call the right tools with only the necessary frequency, rather than simply calling tools as many times as possible.",
    "Even on DRB, where DR Tulu issues more web search and browsing calls, it still remains about 10 times cheaper than Tongyi Deep Research."
  ]
}